$ ORA-14451: unsupported feature with temporary table

Trying to create a → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/types/temporary/private[private temporary table] with a
`not null`, unique or primary key constraint throws the error message *ORA-14451: unsupported feature with temporary table*:
code {
create private temporary table ora$ptt_x (
   id  integer not null,
   txt varchar2(10)
);

create private temporary table ora$ptt_x (
   id  integer unique,
   txt varchar2(10)
);

create private temporary table ora$ptt_x (
   id  integer primary key,
   txt varchar2(10)
);
code }

However, this one is ok:
code {
create private temporary table ora$ptt_x (
   id  integer,
   txt varchar2(10)
);
code }


sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/errors[Other Oracle error messages]
